<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f104809547692944">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=19919&amp;mid=104809547692944">RE: Easy Switch?</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=19919&amp;mid=104809547692944#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Mar 19th 1:12 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=191078"><span id="Scholar">FightClub</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">91 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.80]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>To switch a shield with offhand weapons using the standard UI you can drag the 'offhand item' square from the inventory into one of your macro button positions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then you drag your weapons bag picture from the inventory into an adjacent macro slot.  To swap your offhand contents, click on the weapons bag to open it (move the bag close to your macro bar and 'lock' the bag window so it doesn't move around) and pick the item you want to swap, click on the offhand weapon macro button next and the contents of your hand will switch... now just put the old weapon back in the open bag and close the bag.<br/>You don't have to open the bag - you can either leave it open the whole time if you arrange your UI well, or you can put the shield into the root slot where your weapons bag was and swap directly from there.<br/>Just in case you don't know already... to get an inventory or item slot onto the macro bar, just open the inventory and left click on the thing you want to move, but hold the left mouse button down until the whole square will come up and onto your cursor.<br/><br/>Custom UI's normally do a very similar trick to this but they have the contents of their 'extra' buttons hardwired in the code.  Sars 3.0 UI has a very detailed instruction file telling you how to alter the code, but unless you really need the extra button space I'd stick with the default UI for most things because you don't have to keep patching it every time EQ changes!<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Chrowl, Bria<br/><br/>Artisan, Brawler, Entertainer, Marksman, Medic, Scout<br/>Architect, Combat Medic, Creature Handler, Doctor, Droid Engineer, Fencer (1), Image Designer, Merchant (2), Rifleman (3 then silent), Swordsman, TKA, Weaponsmith, Armorsmith, Squad Leader, Ranger, Tailor, Chef, Dancer, Musician, Carbineer, Pistoleer, Smuggler, Commando<br/><br/>still to go: Bounty Hunter,&nbsp;&nbsp;Bio-Engineer, (working on) Pikeman</td></tr>
