	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=79540"><span id=" ">Wulfrem</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">12 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The idea of switching it out is that you bash with the shield, then switch back to dual wield - until the bash button pops up again. Then swap it in, bash, swap out. You're not losing any bashes; you're just gaining the DPS from swapping the offhand weapon in there between bashes. And the swap can be done quickly enough that you don't lose any swings in between.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
